name: T0
Description: initial number of target cells

name: E0toT0
Description: effector:target ratio

name: Estar0
Description: initial number of depleted effector cells

name: g
Description: tumor cell growth rate 1/hour (Z138 cell line)

name: r
Description: number of effector cells need to kill one target cell

name: kexp
Description: rate of recovery of effector cells from E* --> E 1/hours

name: gamma
Description: slope relating complex formation to ADCC rate

name: CD20
Description: number of CD20 molecules per  um^2 (Z138 cell line)

name: CD16
Description: number of CD16 molecules per um^2

name: RTX
Description: Rituximab concentration in nM

name: kon20
Description: binding on rate of RTX to CD20

name: koff20
Description: binding off rate of RTX to CD20

name: kon16
Description: binding on rate of RTX to CD16 (V158 SNP variant)
Ref: J. Bio. Chem., Jan 3, 2007, doi.org/10.1074/jbc.M609064200 // took average of two variants because variant unknown

name: koff16
Description: binding off rate of RTX to CD16

name: h
Description: height of synapse in nm?

name: gammaPerf
Description: amount of perforin on an Estar cell?

name: RESERVED
Description: Don’t alter capitalized names! Experiment column names must be of form E1_descriptor, E2_descriptor, …

name: DATAPATH
Description: path where data resides, relative to code/. Directory

name: DATAFILE
Description: CSV file where data resides, relative to DATAPATH

name: XNAME
Description: used for labeling X axis

name: YNAME
Description: used for matching model outputs to observations, or just Y label???

name: XHEADER
Description: name of header for X variable (independent variable) in data file

name: YHEADER
Description: name of header for Y variable(s) (observation) in data file. If multiple observation types, use cell array notation {'varA','varB'}

name: YERROR
Description: Column name of Standard deviations of the observations

name: MODEL
Description: name of model file, expected to take in a parameter structure and a vector of X values, in that order, and return Y values with as many rows as length(X) and as many columns as measurement types

name: WEIGHT
Description: NOT YET SUPPORTED: differential weighting of each experiment
